<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-716-744  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 716 744.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  August 6 1990 n478 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UB plots network fault tolerance. (Ungermann-Bass Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Melo, Alfred.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ungermann-Bass Inc is developing a fault-tolerant local areanetwork (LAN)with redundant components.andP;  Fault-tolerancenetworking means assuring the availability of a network 100percent of the time.andP;  It is achieved by using two identicalnetwork components running simultaneously or by having a standbysystem in case of failure.andP;  UB's new fault tolerant LAN willutilize two adapter cards for connecting PCs; two physicalbackbones, either hierarchical or ring topology; and two physicalconnections.andP;  UB believes users will elect a hierarchical startopology as a fault-tolerant solution.andP;  As a related effort to itswork in fault tolerance, UB is also working on Fiber DistributedData Interface (FDDI), with special emphasis on FDDI's dual-ringconfiguration, considered vital to fault-tolerant technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ungermann-Bass (product development).andO;Ticker:    TDM.andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentFault ToleranceNetwork SoftwareLocal Area NetworksBusiness PlanningFiber Distributed Data Interface Standard.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>